genresAdvancedInfo.name: sotalaulut
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Sotalaulut is a Finnish folk music genre that originated in the early 20th century. It is characterized by melancholic melodies, slow tempos, and lyrics that often deal with themes of love, loss, and nature. The genre is often performed with an acoustic guitar and a singing voice.
